<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-458-063  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 458 063.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Telephony  Sept 24 1990 v219 n14 p10(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>FCC approves LEC price-cap plan to mixed reviews. (FederalCommunications Commission; local exchange carrier) (News of theWeek)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Mason, Charles.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>The Federal Communications Commission (FCC) enacts a price-capplan for interstate services provided by local exchange carriers(LECs).andP;  The plan somewhat disappoints the local exchangeindustry.andP;  The price-cap scheme, which will be mandatory for Bellregional holding companies and GTE/Contel as of Jan 1, 1991,contains compromises and includes changes from earlier proposals.andO;The plan includes a higher productivity factor of 3.3 percent,which is not attractive to LECs, and there is a 'sharing'mechanism that caps what LECs can earn.andP;  When a certain limit isreached, LECs must share revenues with customers.andP;  FCC Chmn AlfredSikes, a champion of price caps, believes the plan will be goodfor everyone.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     United States. Federal Communications CommissionBell Regional Holding CompaniesGovernment RegulationPricing PolicyTelephone Companies.andO;Feature:   illustrationportrait.andO;Caption:   Alfred Sikes. (portrait)andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>